  "Q1". "Difference between Severity and Priority?"
  Answer:
  Severity = Impact of the defect on functionality
  Priority = Urgency to fix

  Example:

  Login button not working → High Severity + High Priority
  Typo in homepage → Low Severity + High Priority
  
  "Q2". "What is STLC?"
  Answer:

  Software Testing Life Cycle:

  Requirement Analysis
  Test Planning
  Test Case Development
  Environment Setup
  Test Execution
  Test Closure
  
"Q3". "Difference between Regression and Retesting?"
Answer:
Retesting → Verify fixed defect
Regression → Ensure existing functionality is unaffected
  
"Q4. What are Smoke and Sanity Testing?"
Answer:
Smoke → Broad level testing of critical functionalities
Sanity → Narrow level testing after small changes

"Q5. Difference between var, let, and const?"

Feature	   var	     let	  const
Scope	    Function	Block	  Block
Reassign	  Yes	     Yes	    No
Redeclare	  Yes	      No	    No
  

"Q6. What is Hoisting?"

Answer:

JavaScript moves declarations to the top during compilation.

console.log(a);
var a = 10;

Equivalent
var a;
console.log(a);
a = 10;

"Q7. Difference between == and ===?"
Answer:
== → compares values only
=== → compares value + datatype

Example:
5 == "5"   // true
5 === "5"  // false


